00:38:59.296 --> 00:39:00.546 A:middle
from the spinning gear menu.

00:39:00.606 --> 00:39:04.706 A:middle
But, when it's done, all you
get is just the gear disappears.

00:39:04.706 --> 00:39:06.506 A:middle
You'd like some better
notification of this.

00:39:07.046 --> 00:39:10.626 A:middle
And in the past you'd use
a modal dialog to do this,

00:39:10.626 --> 00:39:12.746 A:middle
but that's really the
wrong interaction method

00:39:13.106 --> 00:39:15.826 A:middle
because a modal dialog
is an alert.

00:39:16.056 --> 00:39:18.436 A:middle
It is saying, "Oh, oh, here.

00:39:18.616 --> 00:39:19.256 A:middle
Sir, sir, sir.

00:39:19.306 --> 00:39:20.146 A:middle
You've got to see this.

00:39:20.226 --> 00:39:21.946 A:middle
You've got to do
something about this.

00:39:22.096 --> 00:39:22.776 A:middle
It's right here.

00:39:23.176 --> 00:39:26.466 A:middle
Are you even paying
attention to this?"

00:39:27.956 --> 00:39:31.296 A:middle
Whereas a notification
is much more passive.

00:39:31.826 --> 00:39:34.096 A:middle
It says, "Oh, hi.

00:39:34.166 --> 00:39:38.516 A:middle
So, yeah. This thing
happened and, yeah.

00:39:38.516 --> 00:39:40.426 A:middle
If you want I can hook you
up with, you know, a guy.

00:39:40.856 --> 00:39:43.476 A:middle
But, you know, if
you don't, it's cool.

00:39:44.906 --> 00:39:46.816 A:middle
See you [laughter]."

00:39:47.706 --> 00:39:49.716 A:middle
And that's what we just got

00:39:49.836 --> 00:39:51.526 A:middle
if you weren't paying
attention as it flowed by.

00:39:52.416 --> 00:39:53.756 A:middle
Our notification showed up and,

00:39:53.756 --> 00:39:56.396 A:middle
if we look in Notification
Center, it's still there

00:39:56.436 --> 00:39:58.236 A:middle
if we happen to be away at
a coffee break or something.

00:39:59.386 --> 00:40:01.236 A:middle
So let's see how we did that.

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:39:59.386 --> 00:40:01.236 A:middle
So let's see how we did that.

00:40:01.666 --> 00:40:05.076 A:middle
I have it open in
Automator over here.

00:40:05.786 --> 00:40:09.556 A:middle
So the basic workflow Sal
explained to you already,

00:40:09.746 --> 00:40:14.136 A:middle
filter out the movies, encode
them, encode them, add the name,

00:40:14.136 --> 00:40:15.536 A:middle
encode then again, add
the different name.

00:40:15.896 --> 00:40:19.146 A:middle
And, at the end, we have display
notification, finished encoding.

00:40:19.936 --> 00:40:22.346 A:middle
So this is nice, but we
can do a little better.

00:40:22.846 --> 00:40:24.386 A:middle
We'd like to get a notification

00:40:24.386 --> 00:40:28.046 A:middle
about what items
just got encoded

00:40:28.506 --> 00:40:31.166 A:middle
because we might have several
of these in flight at once.

00:40:32.986 --> 00:40:36.556 A:middle
Now, we happen to already
have the input file stored

00:40:36.556 --> 00:40:37.236 A:middle
in a variable.

00:40:37.236 --> 00:40:39.646 A:middle
We had to save them
because we were going to --

00:40:39.646 --> 00:40:43.216 A:middle
we have to feed them into two
different encode media actions.

00:40:44.116 --> 00:40:47.706 A:middle
So we can just take
that variable and put it

00:40:47.706 --> 00:40:50.716 A:middle
into the message here because
all these fields support --

00:40:50.716 --> 00:40:51.946 A:middle
support variables.

00:40:53.506 --> 00:40:54.056 A:middle
Save that.

00:40:55.466 --> 00:40:57.746 A:middle
And now, if we do
our workflow again --

00:40:57.746 --> 00:40:59.266 A:middle
I'm using a shorter
movie this time

00:40:59.656 --> 00:41:01.086 A:middle
so it won't take quite as long.

WEBVTT
